1:# Role Feature Matrix
2:
3:Pass: `role-surface-pass`
4:Date: 2026-04-15
5:
6:Map each role to the visible UI it can reach, the backend authorization that actually applies, and the hidden or indirect paths that can still expose the same surface.
7:
8:## Role Matrix
9:
10:| Role | Visible UI | Backend authorization | Hidden or indirect paths | Notes |
11:| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
12:| Public / unauthenticated | Portal chooser, academic login screen, sysadmin login screen, public faculty list | Only the public faculty list is open (`GET /api/academic/public/faculty`); session, bootstrap, and admin APIs require auth | `#/app` and `#/admin` still render portal shells, but the workspaces immediately block on session state | No protected workspace state is available without a session. |
13:| Course Leader | `Dashboard`, `Queue History`, `Calendar / Timetable`, `Data Entry Hub`, course pages, student pages, faculty profile button | Session login and `POST /api/session/role-context`; `GET /api/academic/bootstrap`; course-leader-owned offering reads/writes; `tasks`, `task-placements`, `calendar-audit`, `meetings`, and offering config routes are scope-gated; `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` require active-run + student scope | `scheme-setup` and `entry-workspace` are launched from course/upload actions; `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are launched from student cards and proof controls | Visible UI is broader than backend write scope. The page helper can show a route, but the server still checks offering ownership and student enrollment. |
14:| Mentor | `My Mentees`, `Queue History`, `Calendar / Timetable`, faculty profile button | Session login and `role-context`; `GET /api/academic/bootstrap`; mentor-scoped task and meeting creation; `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` require active-run + student scope | `mentee-detail`, `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are reached from mentee cards and history links, not from top-level nav | Mentor UI is narrow, but indirect student drilldowns remain first-class routes. |
15:| HoD | `Department`, `Queue History`, `Calendar / Timetable`, unlock-review actions in the queue, faculty profile button | Session login and `role-context`; `GET /api/academic/bootstrap`; HoD proof bundle endpoints; governed request list/create; faculty profile reads with department/branch overlap checks; HOD-scoped offering and student access checks; `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` require active-run + student scope | `unlock-review` is not a top-level nav item but is opened from queue actions or direct hashes; `faculty-profile` can target any faculty only when the overlap check passes | HoD is the only academic role with dedicated proof-summary/bundle/courses/faculty/students/reassessments reads. |
16:| SYSTEM_ADMIN | `#/admin` overview, proof dashboard, faculties, students, faculty members, requests, history, and canonical proof hierarchy drilldowns | All `/api/admin/*` families, proof sandbox routes, session restore/logout/role-context, `faculty-profile` self/admin/HOD read path, `student-shell`, `risk-explorer`, and preferences | `#/admin/faculties/:.../batches/:...` is the canonical proof route; `#/admin/history` is the hidden-records surface; search can route into students, faculty, and requests without using the visible tabs | `SystemAdminSessionBoundary` blocks the workspace unless the active session role is `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, even if the user is logged in under another grant. |
17:
18:## Permission Gates
19:
20:- `canAccessPage()` is a client-side gate only. It keeps the academic router from staying on a disallowed page, but it does not replace backend auth.
21:- `resolveRoleSyncState()` snaps disallowed role/page combinations back to the role home page.
22:- `/api/session/role-context` only switches among the session's `availableRoleGrants`; it does not mint a new grant.
23:- `requireRole()` is the first backend gate on the protected routes. It checks the active grant only.
24:- `assertViewerCanReadOffering()`, `assertViewerCanSuperviseStudent()`, `assertCourseLeaderCanManageOffering()`, `resolveProofReassessmentAccess()`, and `evaluateStudentShellSessionMessageAccess()` add the role/scope-specific checks.
25:- `GET /api/academic/faculty-profile/:facultyId` is self-access for the same faculty, or HoD/admin access with a department/branch overlap check.
26:- `GET /api/academic/hod/proof-*` endpoints require `HOD` plus faculty context.
27:- `GET /api/academic/student-shell/*` and `GET /api/academic/students/:studentId/risk-explorer` accept academic roles and `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, but still enforce proof-run and student-scope checks.
28:
29:## Hidden Or Indirect Access Paths
30:
31:- The academic sidebar always exposes a `Faculty Profile` button, but backend access is still self/HOD/admin scoped.
32:- `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are cross-cutting routes reached from student cards, mentee cards, queue rows, and proof controls.
33:- `unlock-review` is reachable from queue actions and direct hashes, even though it is not a top-level sidebar item.
34:- `#/admin/proof-dashboard` and the canonical proof hierarchy route are route-level entry points, not visible top tabs.
35:- `#/admin/history` is a hidden-records workspace, but admin search can still surface requests from that section.
36:- Academic role options in the teaching portal are derived from the current bootstrap snapshot, so proof scope can hide roles that still exist in the underlying session.
37:
38:## Role Drift Likely
39:
40:- The academic UI derives `allowedRoles` from the proof-scoped bootstrap, while `/api/session/role-context` uses the underlying session grants. That can make a role appear unavailable in the UI even when it is still switchable.
41:- The app auto-corrects illegal pages back to the role home page, so a deep link can briefly exist in history without being durable.
42:- `Faculty Profile` is visibly available to every academic role, but the backend rejects out-of-scope HoD reads, so the UI affordance is broader than the authorization surface.
43:- `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` are easy to reach indirectly, but their server-side scope checks are stricter than the route names imply.
44:
45:## Role-Specific Unknowns
46:
47:- The exact narrowing behavior of `resolveStudentShellRun()` and `assertStudentShellScope()` still needs live confirmation.
48:- The live proof-scoped bootstrap may hide some active session grants in the UI, but the session still retains them; the full impact on role switching is only partially verified.
49:- The HoD faculty-profile overlap check is confirmed by test coverage, but the live deployment path still needs an authenticated end-to-end check.

