-## Permission Gates
+## Cross-Role Truth Coupling
 
-- `canAccessPage()` is a client-side gate only. It keeps the academic router from staying on a disallowed page, but it does not replace backend auth.
-- `resolveRoleSyncState()` snaps disallowed role/page combinations back to the role home page.
-- `/api/session/role-context` only switches among the session's `availableRoleGrants`; it does not mint a new grant.
-- `requireRole()` is the first backend gate on the protected routes. It checks the active grant only.
-- `assertViewerCanReadOffering()`, `assertViewerCanSuperviseStudent()`, `assertCourseLeaderCanManageOffering()`, `resolveProofReassessmentAccess()`, and `evaluateStudentShellSessionMessageAccess()` add the role/scope-specific checks.
-- `GET /api/academic/faculty-profile/:facultyId` is self-access for the same faculty, or HoD/admin access with a department/branch overlap check.
-- `GET /api/academic/hod/proof-*` endpoints require `HOD` plus faculty context.
-- `GET /api/academic/student-shell/*` and `GET /api/academic/students/:studentId/risk-explorer` accept academic roles and `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, but still enforce proof-run and student-scope checks.
+- Student truth is split across course leader, mentor, HoD, and sysadmin views.
+- Course truth is operational in course leader, proof-scoped in HoD, and structural in sysadmin.
+- Proof-run truth is shared by academic roles, but sysadmin can inspect inactive runs and checkpoints.
+- Faculty truth is shared across faculty-profile, HoD overlap checks, and sysadmin registries.
+- Request truth is requester-scoped for HoD list/create but operational for sysadmin review.
 
-## Hidden Or Indirect Access Paths
+## Public / unauthenticated
 
-- The academic sidebar always exposes a `Faculty Profile` button, but backend access is still self/HOD/admin scoped.
-- `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are cross-cutting routes reached from student cards, mentee cards, queue rows, and proof controls.
-- `unlock-review` is reachable from queue actions and direct hashes, even though it is not a top-level sidebar item.
-- `#/admin/proof-dashboard` and the canonical proof hierarchy route are route-level entry points, not visible top tabs.
-- `#/admin/history` is a hidden-records workspace, but admin search can still surface requests from that section.
-- Academic role options in the teaching portal are derived from the current bootstrap snapshot, so proof scope can hide roles that still exist in the underlying session.
